external_knowledge:
- "highest-paid" refers to the player with the highest salary;
- "fewer than two injuries" means the player has 0 or 1 injuries;
- "above-average home score" means the team's average home score is greater than the average home score across all teams.

- 'Total salary' refers to the sum of all player salaries for a team;
- 'Number of players' is the count of distinct players on a team;
- 'Average salary' is the mean salary of players on a team;
- 'Total attendance' is the sum of the number of spectators at all games involving the team, either as the home or away team.

- "Victorious home games" refers to games where the home team scored more than the away team;
- "Drawn more than 50,000 spectators" means the total attendance across these winning games exceeds 50,000;
- "Shining bright like stars in a crowded sky" is a metaphorical expression emphasizing the standout performance and popularity of these teams.
